Codex brief APPROVE iter 1 (zero P0/P1) per Codex iter-3 P3 nudge to derive
template set from registry instead of hardcoding.

Before (I-arch-001a): all 7 non-clinical templates collapsed to "policy"
After (this PR): 3 templates with existing config/scope_templates/*.yaml
(ai_sovereignty, canada_us, workforce from I-tpl-006/7/8) promoted to
identity mappings; 4 templates without scope_templates (climate, defense,
housing, trade) keep the "policy" fallback pending Phase 2 authoring.

scope_gate.SUPPORTED_DOMAINS:
- clinical, policy, tech, due_diligence, custom (base)
- ai_sovereignty, canada_us, workforce (I-tpl-006/7/8) ← now used

Tests (4 new, all pass):
- every v6 template_id from registry.list_template_ids() has a mapping
- every mapping value is in SUPPORTED_DOMAINS (would otherwise raise at
  run_scope_gate load_scope_template call)
- promoted templates use identity mapping
- Phase 2 deferred templates fall back to "policy"

